// Secrets.xcconfig.example — committed template. Safe to check in (no real values).
//
// SETUP
//   1. Copy this file:            cp Secrets.xcconfig.example Secrets.xcconfig
//   2. Fill in the two values in Secrets.xcconfig with your Supabase credentials
//      (Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → Data API / API Keys).
//   3. Attach Secrets.xcconfig as the Genesyx target's base configuration, either:
//        • Xcode: Project "Genesyx" → Info → Configurations → for the Genesyx
//          target, set BOTH Debug and Release to `Secrets.xcconfig`, OR
//        • project.yml (if regenerating with xcodegen):
//            targets:
//              Genesyx:
//                configFiles:
//                  Debug: Secrets.xcconfig
//                  Release: Secrets.xcconfig
//   4. Remove the empty inline SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY entries from the
//      target's Build Settings — a target-level value OVERRIDES this file.
//
// Value flow: Secrets.xcconfig → build settings → Info.plist ($(SUPABASE_URL) /
//   $(SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)) → RemoteConfig at runtime. Leave blank for local-only v1.
//
// Secrets.xcconfig is git-ignored (.gitignore); this .example file is not.

// NOTE: "//" in an https URL is an xcconfig comment marker and would truncate the
// value to "https:". The `$()` (empty expansion) between the slashes prevents that —
// it resolves to nothing at build time, yielding a normal https:// URL.
SUPABASE_URL = https:/$()/YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co

// Publishable / anon key (the public client key — safe to ship in the app binary).
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = YOUR-ANON-OR-PUBLISHABLE-KEY
